# Extend Bible Slide Grouping Logic for Dual Monitors

This plan extends the Phase 25 Bible grouping logic (which only applied to Monitor 1) to support both Monitor 1 and Monitor 2 independently based on their respective settings (max verses, max characters, format), while fulfilling complex UI and keyboard navigation requirements.

## User Review Required / Assumptions

> [!WARNING]
> **Typo Assumption in Scenario 4**: In the prompt describing Scenario 4, the example was: Monitor 1 has Max Verses = 2, Monitor 2 has Max Verses = 1.
> The prompt stated: *"when user clicks on 2nd verse, display the 2nd verse in **Monitor 1**. but Monitor 2 projection remains same... so user can use right and left arrows for navigating the slides in **Monitor 1** in this case. (generally whichever Monitor settings has less no. of verses per slide)"*
> Since Monitor 2 has the LESS number of verses (1 verse), I am assuming "Monitor 1" was accidentally written here instead of "Monitor 2". 
> The implementation will assume: clicking the 2nd verse updates Monitor 2 (which has max verses = 1) to show just verse 2, while Monitor 1 (which has max verses = 2) continues displaying verses 1 & 2. Right/Left arrows will also control Monitor 2 (the one with fewer verses).

> [!TIP]
> **Right/Left arrow behavior when settings are identical**: If both Monitor 1 and Monitor 2 have the exact same `maxVerses` setting, the Right/Left arrows will simply behave identically to the Down/Up arrows (moving to the next block of grouped verses).

## Proposed Changes

### `live_projector_providers.dart`
#### [MODIFY] [live_projector_providers.dart](file:///c:/Users/bhanu/projects/KeryxPro/lib/features/live_controller/presentation/live_projector_providers.dart)
- Create a generic `_getGroups(slides, start, end, maxVerses, maxChars)` function.
- Create `m1ActiveSlideIndicesProvider` and `m2ActiveSlideIndicesProvider` to partition Bible blocks independently. (Includes logic for Scenario 3: picking least chars if maxVerses are equal).
- Replace `activeSlideProvider` with `m1ActiveSlideProvider` and `m2ActiveSlideProvider`.
- Update `activeSlideIndicesProvider` to return the **union** of M1 and M2 indices. This drives the background highlighting.
- Add `borderActiveSlideIndicesProvider` which returns the active indices of the monitor with the **lesser** `maxVerses`. This drives the left border highlight.
- Add a new helper provider `slideNavigationProvider` to calculate what the next index should be when Down/Up (moves group of larger monitor) and Right/Left (moves group of smaller monitor) are pressed.

